  <subfield code="a">On black hole radiation spectrum in loop quantum gravity</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">Springer</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">We propose an alternative analysis of black hole entropy from loop quantum gravity (LQG) to reconcile Hawkingâ€™s semiclassical results with the statistical mechanics treatment of LQG for all values of the Barbero-Immirzi (BI) parameter. In particular, using the average area of the punctures, we have calculated the corresponding entropy, identified the BI parameter and derived the radiation spectrum in terms of the possible punctures.</subfield>
